comments: Bridges (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Miller (NOP) and gives him space to avoid the contact.
Booker (PHX) extends his leg as part of a natural shooting motion and the contact with Miller (NOP) does not affect his ability to contest the jump shot attempt.
Bender (PHX) makes marginal contact to Randle's (NOP) body during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Bridges (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Miller (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jackson (NOP) legally contest Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Randle (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bridges (PHX) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bender (PHX) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Miller (NOP) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Miller (NOP) makes marginal contact to Bridges (PHX) and does not affect his FOM.
Booker (PHX) makes marginal contact with Jackson (NOP) as he steps back for his shot attempt and does not affect his ability to defend the shot.
Jackson (NOP) legally contests the jump shot attempt by Booker (PHX).
Oubre Jr. (PHX) does not make contact to Randle's (NOP) arm and makes clean contact to the ball during the drive.
Bender (PHX) cleanly dislodges the ball from Randle (NOP) on his driving shot attempt.
Randle (NOP) has his arms extended when he disengages with Bridges (PHX) but he does not dislodge him from his position.
Miller (NOP) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Booker's (PHX) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Payton (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bridges (PHX) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Oubre Jr. (PHX) legally contests Jackson's (NOP) jump shot attempt.
Randle (NOP) makes contact with Jackson's (PHX) head attempting the block the dunk attempt.
Bender (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NOP) during his drive.
Miller (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Booker (PHX) during his driving shot attempt.
LLB shows Bender (PHX) steps out of bounds before making contact with the ball.
Randle (NOP) and Bender (PHX) briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
Booker (PHX) makes marginal contact with Randle (NOP) and does not affect his SQBR.
Milles (NOP) sets the screen on Bender (PHX) and does not deliver contact.
Bender (PHX) moves laterally into Randle (NOP) and affects his SQBR
RAR shows Booker (PHX) grabs Williams's (NOP) shoulder and makes contact to his arm that affects his shot at the basket.
Randler (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position during Oubre Jr.'s (PHX) driving shot attempt.
Randle (NOP) sets the screen in Jackson's (PHX) path and absorbs the contact.
Jackson (NOP) and Spalding (PHX) briefly engage and separate after the screen.
Jackson (NOP) and Clark (NOP) briefly engage and separate as the players move to the same spot on the floor.
Oubre Jr. (PHX) extends his forearm into Williams (NOP) and initiates contact that affects his ability to defend.
Jackson (PHX) makes contact with Jackson's (NOP) arm and affects his ability to control the pass.
RLB shows Randle (NOP) makes contact with Oubre Jr.'s (PHX) arm and affects his ability to gather the rebound.
Bridges (PHX) makes contact with Randle's (NOP) arm and affects his ability to pass.
Spalding (PHX) sets the screen on Miller (NOP) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Miller (NOP) attempts to commit a take foul on Booker (PHX) as he extends his arm across Booker's body to initiate contact.
Payton (NOP) signals for a timeout during the inbound, but it occurs after five seconds elapses and a five-second violation is called.  The Pelicans had no timeouts remaining at the time.
Payton (NOP) fails to inbound the ball within five seconds.
Daniels (PHX) and Miller (NOP) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Miller (NOP) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
All technical fouls are reviewed by League Operations.
Williams (NOP) commits a take foul on Jackson (PHX).
